explanation: The solution uses Kahn's algorithm to detect cycles in a directed graph. It builds an adjacency list and in-degree vector to represent the course prerequisites. It then processes courses with no incoming edges (in-degree 0) using a queue, decrementing the in-degree of dependent courses and adding them to the queue if their in-degree becomes 0. If all courses are processed, there are no cycles, and it's possible to finish all courses.

